{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af81f3b0-0c52-4a03-9f0d-3fea9815db2e","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update both base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100 SDK is installed\ndotnet build            # ensure it compiles\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso check any NuGet package references (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) — update them to their 11.x versions. Run `dotnet list package --outdated` to find them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38b0b28e-a46b-4522-bfa5-a8965ef65e44","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"B01C:348511:CDAEDF:EDA0AA:69F2B411"},"id":"5d4c4001-9207-41ab-bf20-e238c220ad21","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:44:56.415Z","parentId":"fdad9947-13cc-4a84-9cfe-4ee6411138f1"}
